hor" data-v-bcda89eb><!--[--><a class="hero-review-score-header__author-link" href="https://www.jeuxactu.com/test-lego-batman-le-meilleur-jeu-batman-depuis-arkham-knight-est-un-je-131827.htm" rel="follow" target="_blank"><!--[--><span title="JeuxActu" data-v-bcda89eb>JeuxActu</span><!--]--></a><!--]--></div></div><div class="hero-review-card__quote" data-v-6413b726>LEGO Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight is the kind of game we thought we’d never see again. A title that successfully revives the spirit of the Batman Arkham series while keeping the accessible, chaotic charm of classic LEGO games intact. What could have been a lazy nostalgia trip instead turns into a sincere, ambitious, and surprisingly polished love letter to the Dark Knight. Behind its LEGO humor and family-friendly tone lies a game that genuinely understands Batman: his mythology, his villains, his films, his comics, and his video game legacy. TT Games blends all of these influences together with impressive confidence to create an adventure that feels both like a celebration of the character and a genuinely great action-adventure game. Sure, the low difficulty, basic enemy AI, and a few technical hiccups hold it back from true masterpiece territory. But despite those flaws, LEGO Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight captures something special: the fantasy of soaring across Gotham at night, striking fear into criminals, and truly feeling like Batman again. TT Games hasn’t just made its best LEGO game in years, it’s delivered one of the best Batman tributes ever made.</div><button type="button" data-v-6413b726 data-slot="base" class="font-medium aria-disabled:cursor-not-allowed aria-disabled:opacity-75 inline-flex items-center no-underline cursor-pointer border-solid ring-0 shadow-none outline-0 rounded-[0.3rem] transition-all duration-[150ms] ease-[ease] focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-current focus-visible:outline-offset-0.5 disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed disabled:pointer-events-none [object Object] h-8 text-sm leading-[26px] justify-center border border-gray-600 bg-gray-800 text-white hover:bg-gray-600 active:bg-gray-600 px-4 [&amp;_svg]:stroke-white global-button--dark hero-review-card__read-more-button"><!--[--><!--[--><!----><!--]--><!--[--><!--[--><span class="leading-normal whitespace-nowrap overflow-hidden text-ellipsis"><!--[-->Read More<!--]--></span><!----><!--]--><!--]--><!--[--><!----><!--]--><!--]--></button><div class="hero-review-card__footer" data-v-6413b726><div class="hero-review-card__date" data-v-6413b726>May 19, 2026</div><div class="hero-review-card__platform" data-v-6413b726>PlayStation 5</div></div></div><!--teleport start--><!--teleport end--><!--]--><!--]--><!--[--><!--[--><div class="hero-review-card" data-v-6413b726><div class="hero-review-score-header hero-review-card__header" data-v-6413b726 data-v-bcda89eb><div class="hero-review-score-header__score" data-v-bcda89eb><div class="c-siteReviewScore_background c-siteReviewScore_background-critic_small" data-v-bcda89eb><div class="c-siteReviewScore c-siteReviewScore_green c-siteReviewScore_small c-siteReviewScore_square bg-[#00ce7a] text-[#262626] size-10 text-base leading-6 rounded-[0.25rem] flex flex-col items-center justify-center font-bold" title="Metascore 80 out of 100" aria-label="Metascore 80 out of 100"><span>80</span></div></div></div><div class="hero-review-score-header__author" data-v-bcda89eb><!--[--><a class="hero-review-score-header__author-link" href="https://www.dexerto.com/gaming/lego-batman-legacy-of-the-dark-knight-review-3365905/" rel="follow" target="_blank"><!--[--><span title="Dexerto" data-v-bcda89eb>Dexerto</span><!--]--></a><!--]--></div></div><div class="hero-review-card__quote" data-v-6413b726>Lego Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight takes 87 years of Batman history and crams it into one plastic package. The result is a joyous love letter to the Caped Crusader that feels like every classic Batman movie rolled into one.</div><button t