781-e0a076ad8274","games-awardstracker-2023.jpg",{"date":2549,"timezone":1794},"2023-11-13 23:46:07.000000","Metacritic/Nintendo","https://www.metacritic.com/a/img/2023/11/13/9bc6d222-d8a0-46a1-b781-e0a076ad8274/games-awardstracker-2023.jpg",{"id":2553,"type":1820,"title":2554,"slug":2555,"date":2556,"url":1288,"isVideo":1288,"description":2557,"tags":2558,"author":2560,"image":2561},"e206a2ce-adbc-4515-af55-b39393ce33c6","Lord of the Rings Video Games, Ranked Worst to Best","lord-of-the-rings-video-games-ranked-worst-to-best","2023-05-26 00:01:00","(Updated July 2025) We rank every modern video game inspired by the Lord of the Rings books and films from worst to best by Metascore.",[2559],{"id":1780,"name":1781,"slug":1782},{"byline":1784,"firstName":1785,"id":1786,"lastName":1787,"username":1788},{"id":2562,"filename":2563,"dateCreated":2564,"alt":1288,"credits":1288,"path":2566,"cropGravity":1288,"crop":1288,"caption":2567,"typeName":1288,"imageUrl":1288,"width":2568,"height":2569,"sType":1288,"bucketType":1288,"bucketPath":1288,"mediaType":1288},"42a142cf-0b7b-4639-a8c8-bdc6ee88784b","s2386-gplanding-1685038272.jpg",{"date":2565,"timezone":1794},"2023-08-25 04:22:24.000000","https://www.metacritic.com/a/img/2023/08/25/42a142cf-0b7b-4639-a8c8-bdc6ee88784b/s2386-gplanding-1685038272.jpg","\u003Cp>\u003Cstrong>Xbox 360, 2011\u003C/strong>\u003Cbr>          also on           \u003Ca href=\"https://www.metacritic.com/game/playstation-3/the-lord-of-the-rings-war-in-the-north\">PlayStation 3\u003C/a>, \u003Ca href=\"https://www.metacritic.com/game/pc/the-lord-of-the-rings-war-in-the-north\">PC\u003C/a>\u003C/p>\u003Cp>A hack-and-slash with RPG elements, 2011's \u003Cem>War in the North\u003C/em> was the first game released following Warner Bros. Interactive's 2009 acquisition of the rights to adapt both Tolkien's books and Peter Jackson's films. (Previously, the rights to adapt the book and film franchises were held separately by Vivendi and EA, respectively.) Developed by Snowblind, the studio behind the excellent \u003Cem>Baldur's Gate: Dark Alliance\u003C/em>, the game borrowed its overall look from the films, though it used new voice actors and drew  elements from the books that were not in the movie trilogyâ€\"but it  didn't really share a focus with either, instead depicting a side quest taken on by a trio of playable characters: a ranger, a dwarf, and an elf, who can be played separately or all at once via online co-op. \u003C/p>\u003Cp>Unlike some of the \u003Cem>LOTR\u003C/em> games already discussed, \u003Cem>North\u003C/em> was aimed at older audiences, but that maturity didn't necessarily translate to a better game. Some critics liked the co-op gameplay, but many complained about the poor AI and lack of originality, and quite a few reviewers felt that \u003Cem>North\u003C/em> wore out its welcome after just a few hours.\u003C/p>\u003Cp>â€œLord of the Rings: War in the North is fine for a few hours of jolly good fun, but once you realise that the game has played its hand early and really has nothing else to offer then the lustre is soon lost. Poor AI, boring combat and pointless quests all add up to a disappointing game that would be better off dropped into the fires of Mordor.â€ â€\"Xbox Achievements\u003C/p>",825,490,{"id":2571,"type":1773,"title":2572,"slug":2573,"date":2574,"url":1288,"isVideo":1288,"description":2575,"tags":2576,"author":2579,"image":2585},"bd81a43b-e991-4e3a-9e53-21258f015822","Games Like 'Warhammer 40,000: Darktide' to Play Next","games-like-warhammer-40000-darktide","2022-12-13 17:00:10","As fun as the latest in the franchise is, there are plenty of other cooperative shooters worthy of your time.",[2577],{"id":1780,"name":1301,"slug":2578},"games",{"byline":2580,"firstName":2581,"id":2582,"lastName":2583,"username":2584},"Jon Bitner","Jon","3a150dfe-8f77-45d4-838b-1ea4fd21b6f8","Bitner","jbitner-mc",{"id":2586,"filename":2587,"dateCreated":2588,"alt":1288,"credits":2590,"path":2591,"cropGravit