,"platform":1655},"LEGO Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight is the kind of game we thought we’d never see again. A title that successfully revives the spirit of the Batman Arkham series while keeping the accessible, chaotic charm of classic LEGO games intact. What could have been a lazy nostalgia trip instead turns into a sincere, ambitious, and surprisingly polished love letter to the Dark Knight. Behind its LEGO humor and family-friendly tone lies a game that genuinely understands Batman: his mythology, his villains, his films, his comics, and his video game legacy. TT Games blends all of these influences together with impressive confidence to create an adventure that feels both like a celebration of the character and a genuinely great action-adventure game. Sure, the low difficulty, basic enemy AI, and a few technical hiccups hold it back from true masterpiece territory. But despite those flaws, LEGO Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight captures something special: the fantasy of soaring across Gotham at night, striking fear into criminals, and truly feeling like Batman again. TT Games hasn’t just made its best LEGO game in years, it’s delivered one of the best Batman tributes ever made.","https://www.jeuxactu.com/test-lego-batman-le-meilleur-jeu-batman-depuis-arkham-knight-est-un-je-131827.htm","JeuxActu","jeuxactu",{"id":1733,"type":2578,"title":1651,"url":1362,"criticScoreSummary":3262,"platform":3263,"gameTaxonomy":3265},{"url":1732,"score":1658},{"id":3264,"name":1655},1500000062,{"game":3266,"platform":3267},{"id":1733,"name":1651},{"id":3264,"name":1655},{"quote":3269,"score":2815,"url":3270,"date":1663,"author":1797,"authorSlug":1288,"image":1288,"publicationName":3271,"publicationSlug":3272,"reviewedProduct":3273,"platform":1655},"Lego Batman: Legacy of the Dark Knight takes 87 years of Batman history and crams it into one plastic package. The result is a joyous love letter to the Caped Crusader that feels like every classic Batman movie rolled into one.","htt